{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Refimprove|date=May 2010}} [[File:Nude woman spreading legs 2.jpg|thumb|A nudist woman spreads her legs to show her genital jewellery, [[Nudes-A-Poppin']], USA]] '''Genital jewellery''', also known as '''sex jewellery''' and '''adult jewellery''', is [[jewellery]] which is designed specifically for wear on or to accentuate the [[genital]]s.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=d0NRAyl-2EEC&lpg=PA198&dq=%22genital%20jewellery%22&pg=PA198#v=onepage&q=%22genital%20jewellery%22&f=false Judith Green, Ronald N. Labonté (2007) ''Critical perspectives in public health''], pp198, Routledge. {{ISBN|0-415-40952-7}} Retrieved 17 May 2010</ref> In a wider sense also [[Nipple shield (jewelry)|nipple rings]] and some [[butt-plug]]s may be called genital jewellery.
Genital jewellery includes [[cock ring]]s and [[Labia piercing|vaginal jewellery]] as well as [[anal piercing]]s. These items often blur the line between jewellery and [[sex toys]]. Genital jewellery is available for men and women and some models may be worn by both sexes. While some genital piercings have been around since at least Victorian times (e.g. [[Prince Albert piercing]] jewellery), a recent increase in popularity and social acceptance has resulted in the fusion between function and [[fashion]] that is sex jewellery.
The practice is not new, however, with genital piercings, designed to stimulate as well as to decorate, being described as early as 300 in ''The Kama Sutra''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=DuNTznUH8ZkC&lpg=PA163&dq=%22genital%20jewellery%22&pg=PA163#v=onepage&q=%22genital%20jewellery%22&f=false Guy N. Rutty (2004) ''Essentials Of Autopsy Practice''], 2 Ed., pp 163. Springer, London. {{ISBN|1-85233-967-5}} Retrieved 17 May 2010</ref>
Wearing genital jewellery in nudist resorts may sometimes be considered inappropriate<ref>[http://www.fcn.ca/gn_sample.htm Federation of Canadian Naturalists] Retrieved 17 May 2010</ref> because it may be seen as overtly sexual (see [[Issues_in_social_nudity#Appropriate_dress|Issues in social nudity]]). {| |- | [[File:Eichel gepierct.JPG|left|thumb|200px| Male: Ring on penis head]] | [[File:Piercings close up.jpg|left|thumb|150px|Female: Diamonds on labia]] |}
