A '''hypnozygote''' is a resting [[Microbial cyst|cyst]] resulting from sexual fusion; it is commonly thick-walled. A synonym of [[zygotic]] cyst.<ref>FENSOME R.A., TAYLOR F.J.R., NORRIS G., SARJEANT W.A.S., WHARTON D.I. & WILLIAMS G.L. 1993. A classification of living and fossil dinoflagellates. American Museum of Natural History, Micropaleontology, Special Publication 7: 1-351.</ref>

